\subtree{ \title{Summary}
  \p{This PR continues on from \citek{stt-00BD}, defining more of the foundations
     of simplicial type theory. Key additions include:
     }
  \ul{
    \li{Definition of [comma](stt-00C3) and [cocomma](stt-00CV) types - and derived
        notions such as [slice types](stt-00C4) and the [directed join](stt-00CW).
    }
    \li{Some development of the theory of [extension types](stt-00CL). Including a fix to the
    definition of [Hom2](stt-00AK).}
    \li{The definition of a [variety](stt-00C1) [of](stt-00CR) [subshapes](stt-00CP),
        and development of some more machinery for showing when
        [pushouts are equivalent](stt-00CO) }
    \li{Making use of the [recent orthogonality closure results](stt-00BZ) to show that both
        left and right fibrations are also inner. }
    \li{The definition of [homotopies](Synthetic.Categories.Homotopies),
        and showing they are identity systems for morphisms in precategories.}
  }
}

